0c9d7599-dc7c-4435-a282-d5f3b9913512.name: Terrace
0c9d7599-dc7c-4435-a282-d5f3b9913512.sentence: Located in the Biomedical School, this area has many natural beauties.

1882b4aa-0bcb-4b63-a28f-586053c8b24c.name: Silent Tree

2410e57b-d951-471a-ae79-91100ca82852.name: Untitled
2410e57b-d951-471a-ae79-91100ca82852.sentence: This functional, polished, granite drinking fountain is an exact replica of commercial metal fountains typically found in business offices and government buildings.

2b6740ed-37ba-4795-840f-7c95c79ab3d3.name: READ/WRITE/THINK/DREAM
2b6740ed-37ba-4795-840f-7c95c79ab3d3.sentence: As the doors open and close, the colored panes cross over each other, visually mixing into new colors.

2ca94c6c-b96b-40de-bad3-e2da6671e04a.name: Revelle Plaque
2ca94c6c-b96b-40de-bad3-e2da6671e04a.sentence: Located in the southmost entrance, this plaque contains the core values of Revelle, which are purpose, truth, and vision.

316a34fd-0606-4e23-9a47-85a5a08f9729.name: Standing
316a34fd-0606-4e23-9a47-85a5a08f9729.sentence: Standing calls forth thoughts of human strength and frailty, and both the power and the limits of medicine.

344794bc-5cd3-4342-83cc-36ceac061c46.name: Something Pacific
344794bc-5cd3-4342-83cc-36ceac061c46.sentence: Paik's Something Pacific for the Stuart Collection was his first permanent outdoor installation. This work relates specifically to its site, which includes the lobby of the university's Media Center as well as the lawns surrounding the building.

3919bfd4-f6ad-4c49-847f-4438f86f5e57.name: Snake Path
3919bfd4-f6ad-4c49-847f-4438f86f5e57.sentence: Consists of a winding 560-foot-long, 10-foot-wide footpath in the form of a serpent, whose individual scales are hexagonal pieces of colored slate, and whose head is inlaid in the approach to the Geisel Library.

3dbffeb1-7c76-4318-95df-e671f8c2fa2b.name: Revelle Anchor
3dbffeb1-7c76-4318-95df-e671f8c2fa2b.sentence: Art landmark located in the courtyard in front of 64 Degrees, Revelle's dining hall. This anchor is used as a canvas where students can come and decorate it however they'd like

4552d3f2-bea6-426d-8f1e-c584ce51b537.name: Graffiti Walls
4552d3f2-bea6-426d-8f1e-c584ce51b537.sentence: This a space where students can express themselves and share their art with their peers. It is located right across the LGBT Center and Mandeville.

4addc5f2-077d-41ac-9a23-cd6cc8c8c923.name: Before I Die Board
4addc5f2-077d-41ac-9a23-cd6cc8c8c923.sentence: Board located in the Old Student Center in the hallway conecting the courtyard and the General store, students can freely express their goals here by writing what they would like to do before they die

571b1910-4f4b-468a-b6c3-c3fe3953b25c.name: Vices and Virtues
571b1910-4f4b-468a-b6c3-c3fe3953b25c.sentence: Vices and Virtues for the Stuart Collection consists of seven pairs of words superimposed in blinking neon, which run like a frieze around the top of the Charles Lee Powell Structural Systems Laboratory.

58837abb-768f-49cb-9192-5bab7ec17a96.name: Sky Garden
58837abb-768f-49cb-9192-5bab7ec17a96.sentence: Garden in the rooftop of the West Bar of Keeling Apartments located in the Revelle College. This is a great place to watch the sunset or study with your friends.

6705dc72-f2ae-4e8d-8c4c-096ec79e7b2e.name: La Jolla Project
6705dc72-f2ae-4e8d-8c4c-096ec79e7b2e.sentence: Completed in 1984 and the third work in the Stuart Collection, is located on the Revelle College lawn south of Galbraith Hall.

6a82f7a0-9519-426b-968e-c4e00d170e63.name: Sun God Statue
6a82f7a0-9519-426b-968e-c4e00d170e63.sentence: Sun God has become a landmark on the UCSD campus. Students have at various times embellished the statue with giant sunglasses, a cap and gown, a UCSD ID card, and a nest of hay with eggs.

6b9a7e79-c3d9-4dbe-b3cd-d04e80ace3d6.name: Geisel Library
6b9a7e79-c3d9-4dbe-b3cd-d04e80ace3d6.sentence: Geisel Library is the main library building of the University of California, San Diego Library. It is named in honor of Audrey and Theodor Seuss Geisel, better known as Dr. Seuss.

6bdd9441-54b1-4e02-8d09-0efdbc3e73be.name: Chicano Legacy Mural
6bdd9441-54b1-4e02-8d09-0efdbc3e73be.sentence: The art project was envisioned by students of UC San Diego’s Movimiento Estudiantil Chicano de Aztlán (MEChA) several years ago as a way to express Latino/a culture, and then brought to fruition by world-renowned San Diego-based artist Mario Torero.

71607257-023c-4079-afcf-34ab5c922703.name: Peace Memorial
71607257-023c-4079-afcf-34ab5c922703.sentence: The May 1970 Peace Memorial in its southeast corner commemorates the anti-war self-immolation of Revelle student George Winne, Jr.

75652942-a422-43b9-89af-9e3decbfd22e.name: Another
75652942-a422-43b9-89af-9e3decbfd22e.sentence: Another is in the vast atrium of the Price Center East, a 2008 addition to the original student center.

7b2ed5a0-1363-4dca-9bf1-9cfb2adb195f.name: Singing Tree
7b2ed5a0-1363-4dca-9bf1-9cfb2adb195f.sentence: One could walk through the grove several times before noticing Allen's two unobtrusive trees. Not only do these trees reinvest a natural site with a literal sense of magic but they implicitly make connections between nature and death and the life of the spirit. It is not surprising that students have dubbed this area the 'Enchanted Forest.'

7d00f46e-f56c-4a17-9e2d-88dd4104fb5e.article1: Ian Hamilton Finlay (1925-2006) is best known for "Little Sparta,", a farm and garden in the Southern Uplands of Scotland which he and Sue Finlay began transforming into a neoclassical sculpture park in 1966
7d00f46e-f56c-4a17-9e2d-88dd4104fb5e.article2: They have created temples from farm buildings, and have distributed architectural fragments, fountains, and commemorative plaques interspersed with significant plantings throughout the property.
7d00f46e-f56c-4a17-9e2d-88dd4104fb5e.name: UNDA
7d00f46e-f56c-4a17-9e2d-88dd4104fb5e.sentence: UNDA consists of five stone blocks into which are carved, in various sequences, the letters U, N, D, A, and an S-like mark which is the editor's notation for 'transpose these letters.'

90b5c563-9be6-4f07-aff4-1af3d7d164ce.name: Green Table
90b5c563-9be6-4f07-aff4-1af3d7d164ce.sentence: For the Stuart Collection, Holzer has created Green Table, a large granite picnic or refectory table and benches inscribed with texts.

a62e8e71-1138-4c3e-b99e-a39479c63c27.name: Revelle Fountain
a62e8e71-1138-4c3e-b99e-a39479c63c27.quote: Ambition and love are the wings to great deeds
a62e8e71-1138-4c3e-b99e-a39479c63c27.sentence: Water fountain located in Revelle Plaza, this fountain has been a signature landmark since the early stages of the Revelle college campus

a71487ed-0ca3-4f59-b346-c1a8e7768387.name: Solar Chill
a71487ed-0ca3-4f59-b346-c1a8e7768387.sentence: The Solar Chill project was started by members of Engineers for a Sustainable World in 2013. The project aims to build a 1.5kW off-grid photovoltaic structure and unique social space in the North UCSD campus. The project mission is to provide by-passers with education and inspiration regarding sustainable energy alternatives while also promoting campus unity and providing a safe haven for students to de-stress.

b0da3b62-a561-4046-8dc4-0efaf1233c14.name: Fallen Star
b0da3b62-a561-4046-8dc4-0efaf1233c14.sentence: Fallen Star is the 18th permanent sculpture commissioned by UCSD’s Stuart Collection. It reflects Suh’s on-going exploration of themes around the idea of home, cultural displacement, the perception of our surroundings, and how one constructs a memory of a space.

b312dcfd-85f2-41ed-8937-99cbc09c94dc.name: OceanView

b84c447f-c379-4541-83a0-694806e5dad1.name: Bear
b84c447f-c379-4541-83a0-694806e5dad1.sentence: A bear constructed of boulders. Eight granite stones - torso, head, ears, arms, and legs - were found locally. Together they make a bear 23'6 feet high with a total weight of 180 tons.

b8ecfc8b-2395-42c0-b5f3-ee349e0746bc.name: Glider Port
b8ecfc8b-2395-42c0-b5f3-ee349e0746bc.sentence: The Torrey Pines Gliderport is a city-owned private-use glider airport located in La Jolla, 11 nautical miles northwest of the central business district of City of San Diego, in San Diego County, California.

bf5a5c6e-84b9-4ded-a545-24f9b54486d6.name: The Hump

c836aa06-07fb-4379-a401-bb6602230a09.name: Red Shoe
c836aa06-07fb-4379-a401-bb6602230a09.sentence: Driving along Torrey Pines Road, which borders the campus, or walking an adjacent pedestrian path, viewers gradually decipher a mysterious red object -- a shoe loping through the woods, colorful jewels in its wake.

dd85fd0b-83fc-4720-a45f-c18a40a94136.sentence: The Ché Café is a worker co-operative, social center, and live music venue located on the University of California, San Diego campus in La Jolla, California.
